  "totalStationsApprox": 1100,
  "notes": "Verified against ksp.karnataka.gov.in (Organization page), official unit sites (mysurucitypolice, hubballidharwadcitypolice, bcp, kalaburagicitypolice, tumkurpolice), district NIC portals, and Wikipedia. Key points: (1) Karnataka has 31 revenue districts; Ramanagara district was officially renamed 'Bengaluru South' by gazette notification on 23 May 2025 (HQ remains Ramanagara town; the police unit is still commonly styled Ramanagara District Police) - do not confuse with the Bengaluru South TALUK inside Bengaluru Urban district. (2) KSP has 7 ranges (per official KSP Organization page): Central (Bengaluru), Eastern (Davanagere), Northern (Belagavi), North Eastern (Kalaburagi), Southern (Mysuru), Western (Mangaluru), Ballari (Ballari). Kolar Gold Field (KGF) is a separate POLICE district under Central Range but not a revenue district. Bengaluru District Police (HQ Bengaluru) covers Bengaluru Rural district plus non-city fringes of Bengaluru Urban. (3) 6 city commissionerates confirmed; each covers only the city, with the parent district's remainder under a separate district police unit (SP). Bengaluru CP holds ADGP rank; others DIG/IGP rank. (4) Station counts: Bengaluru City Police has ~108 law-and-order + ~42 traffic stations; Hubballi-Dharwad 15 L&O + 4 traffic + 2 special; Belagavi City 15 incl. women PS; Mangaluru City ~15; Kalaburagi City 10; Shivamogga district 32 stations + 17 outposts. Statewide, KSP reported 1,060 regular police stations in 2023 (Karnataka govt order on cybercrime registration) plus ~48 CEN/cyber and other special-purpose stations, so the ~1100 claim is approximately correct; Wikipedia's 906 figure is older/law-and-order-only - I used 1100 as the approximation. (5) Taluk lists are real but capped at 8 per district for brevity; several districts (Belagavi, Vijayapura, Uttara Kannada, Kalaburagi, Mysuru, Tumakuru) have additional newer taluks (e.g. Nippani, Kittur, Mudalagi, Savadatti; Devara Hipparagi, Kolhar; Haliyal, Joida, Mundgod, Dandeli; Shahabad, Yadrami, Kalagi; Saragur; Tiptur, Turuvekere). Lower-confidence items: 'Koratagere PS' and 'Tumakuru Rural PS' (taluk HQ stations, near-certain but not seen verbatim on the official page fetched); exact spelling variants (e.g. Kasabapeth/Kasbapeth, Malmaruti/Mal Maruti, Kakti/Kakati) follow the official unit websites where available."
}